Yeah, really.
(rattling)

00:34:42,910 --> 00:34:43,612
Ah,

00:34:43,612 --> 00:34:44,514
my brethren.

00:34:44,514 --> 00:34:46,685
I was about to use the
foul modern text device

00:34:46,685 --> 00:34:48,856
to summon you.
What are you doing?

00:34:50,192 --> 00:34:52,497
I beseech you to enter

00:34:52,497 --> 00:34:53,899
my sacred domain.

00:34:57,206 --> 00:35:00,246
I welcome you on the day
of the Mabon Moon...

00:35:00,246 --> 00:35:01,248
David...
...whence we...

00:35:01,248 --> 00:35:02,450
I'm tired.

00:35:02,450 --> 00:35:04,487
I'm spell-casting to prove
a point.
Please.

00:35:04,487 --> 00:35:05,857
Please.

00:35:05,857 --> 00:35:07,494
Fine.

00:35:07,494 --> 00:35:09,732
I understand
that our high priest is mum,

00:35:09,732 --> 00:35:11,469
but his cauldron isn't.

00:35:11,469 --> 00:35:13,205
I ran the ingredients
found in it,

00:35:13,205 --> 00:35:14,341
discovered trace amounts

00:35:14,341 --> 00:35:17,347
of cherry opal gemstone.

00:35:18,783 --> 00:35:19,652
Wiccans believe

00:35:19,652 --> 00:35:22,591
the cherry opal amplifies
vibrational energies

00:35:22,591 --> 00:35:23,660
within the bloodstream.

00:35:23,660 --> 00:35:25,230
We have been assuming

00:35:25,230 --> 00:35:27,936
that this is a power spell,

00:35:27,936 --> 00:35:29,371
but the truth is
this soup's

00:35:29,371 --> 00:35:30,641
a healing spell.

00:35:30,641 --> 00:35:31,743
So, what are you saying?

00:35:31,743 --> 00:35:33,379
That Ed Lusk is sick?

00:35:33,379 --> 00:35:35,484
No, but someone else is.

00:35:35,484 --> 00:35:37,522
Someone who borrowed
Turk's blood

00:35:37,522 --> 00:35:40,595
and availed themselves
to Lusk's altar.

00:35:40,595 --> 00:35:43,300
As I expected,

00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:45,738
I found Turk's blood
in the cauldron.

00:35:45,738 --> 00:35:47,910
But unexpectedly,

00:35:47,910 --> 00:35:50,648
I found
a second blood contributor.

00:35:50,648 --> 00:35:53,387
Not Lusk,
but someone whose blood

00:35:53,387 --> 00:35:56,628
contains traces of methotrexate.

00:35:56,628 --> 00:35:59,901
That's a chemo drug used
to treat blood cancers.

00:35:59,901 --> 00:36:01,236
Thou art correct.

00:36:01,236 --> 00:36:03,942
And Henry hath
run said blood.

00:36:03,942 --> 00:36:06,848
He found a male familial match

00:36:06,848 --> 00:36:08,885
to touch DNA from
a candle recovered

00:36:08,885 --> 00:36:10,289
from Messner's altar.

00:36:10,289 --> 00:36:11,758
The match was not to Ed Lusk,

00:36:11,758 --> 00:36:12,928
but to a different

00:36:12,928 --> 00:36:14,932
wicked witch.

00:36:21,377 --> 00:36:22,647
Ms. Brewer?

00:36:22,647 --> 00:36:26,422
Haven't you asked my son
enough questions?

00:36:26,422 --> 00:36:26,989
Enough is enough.

00:36:26,989 --> 00:36:28,592
We asked you
to bring Mason here

00:36:28,592 --> 00:36:30,830
because we're concerned.

00:36:30,830 --> 00:36:32,534
Concerned?
About what will happen

00:36:32,534 --> 00:36:34,304
to him.

00:36:35,306 --> 00:36:36,943
I don't understand.

00:36:38,846 --> 00:36:41,652
You need to come with me,
Mrs. Brewer.

00:36:42,454 --> 00:36:43,757
Now.

00:36:49,535 --> 00:36:51,840
<i>We know that your son, Mason,</i>
<i>is sick, Rebecca.</i>

00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:55,681
That he has
Langerhans cell histiocytosis.

00:36:55,681 --> 00:36:58,553
The blood cancer
that affects children.

00:36:58,553 --> 00:36:59,889
He missed a lot of school

00:36:59,889 --> 00:37:01,559
last semester.

00:37:01,559 --> 00:37:04,599
His grades started
to falter.

00:37:04,599 --> 00:37:07,605
We know that he was
receiving treatment,

00:37:07,605 --> 00:37:10,845
but <i>you</i> were seeking help
of a higher power.

00:37:10,845 --> 00:37:13,618
I'm not following.

00:37:13,618 --> 00:37:14,887
We found Ed Lusk's cauldron.

00:37:14,887 --> 00:37:17,492
We know that you're the one
who prepared the ritual

00:37:17,492 --> 00:37:18,795
with your son's blood.

00:37:18,795 --> 00:37:19,830
BRODY:
And Turk's.

00:37:19,830 --> 00:37:20,999
You needed it to save Mason.

00:37:20,999 --> 00:37:22,702
CRAWFORD:
You're the one who killed Turk

00:37:22,702 --> 00:37:24,005
and Messner.

00:37:24,005 --> 00:37:25,809
Your original plan
wasn't too bad.

00:37:25,809 --> 00:37:27,479
I mean, you heard the rumblings
around school

00:37:27,479 --> 00:37:30,318
that Turk was looking
for the Chem IV test answers.

00:37:30,318 --> 00:37:32,055
It's pretty easy,
setting him up.

00:37:32,055 --> 00:37:33,792
This is you

00:37:33,792 --> 00:37:36,631
entering the school
library at 1:16.

00:37:36,631 --> 00:37:39,336
That's the same day that
Chet Messner was killed.

00:37:39,336 --> 00:37:40,506
And at 1:19,

00:37:40,506 --> 00:37:41,675
you logged on to a computer

00:37:41,675 --> 00:37:44,046
using Hannah Hunt's password.

00:37:44,046 --> 00:37:45,783
You logged on to VidTree,

00:37:45,783 --> 00:37:49,424
and you sent a message
to Rob Turkla.

00:37:49,424 --> 00:37:51,094
Telling him where to find
the cheat sheet,

00:37:51,094 --> 00:37:53,499
but Messner found it instead.

00:37:53,499 --> 00:37:56,538
CRAWFORD: And so you had
to try and kill Rob again.

00:37:56,538 --> 00:37:58,108
You knew Turk's schedule.

00:37:58,108 --> 00:38:00,747
You knew where to find him.

00:38:08,363 --> 00:38:11,536
Why, Rebecca?

00:38:11,536 --> 00:38:13,406
Was Mason getting worse?

00:38:13,406 --> 00:38:15,610
Why?

00:38:15,610 --> 00:38:17,581
The cancer spread to his bones.

00:38:17,581 --> 00:38:19,652
The doctor found
vertical lesions

00:38:19,652 --> 00:38:21,957
and gave him six months to live.

00:38:21,957 --> 00:38:25,831
So you were running
out of time.

00:38:25,831 --> 00:38:27,401
We get it.

00:38:27,401 --> 00:38:29,873
Why does a piece of crap
like Turk

00:38:29,873 --> 00:38:30,875
get to live?

00:38:30,875 --> 00:38:32,044
Why does a good boy...

00:38:32,779 --> 00:38:34,449
Why does your Mason have to die?

00:38:34,449 --> 00:38:35,718
Where's the harmony in that?

00:38:35,718 --> 00:38:37,555
We searched your car.

00:38:37,555 --> 00:38:39,726
We found your Book of Shadows.

00:38:39,726 --> 00:38:43,434
Inside there was a healing
spell dedicated to Mason.

00:38:44,803 --> 00:38:46,807
The spell's materials

00:38:46,807 --> 00:38:49,579
were all the same items
that we found

00:38:49,579 --> 00:38:50,983
in Ed Lusk's cauldron.

00:38:50,983 --> 00:38:52,485
I can...

00:38:52,485 --> 00:38:54,422
Please.
Listen, I know

00:38:54,422 --> 00:38:56,059
that you love your son.

00:38:56,059 --> 00:38:57,463
No doubt.

00:38:57,463 --> 00:38:58,665
It's all right here.

00:39:01,504 --> 00:39:04,109
"If I could set
my own soul free

00:39:04,109 --> 00:39:06,714
"to save you, I would,

00:39:06,714 --> 00:39:08,485
"but I'm earthbound,

00:39:08,485 --> 00:39:10,856
"so I can call on thee, gods.

00:39:10,856 --> 00:39:15,700
Let the rising sun sear
the cold serpent of disease."

00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:16,869
BOTH:
"My child..."

00:39:18,939 --> 00:39:20,877
"...let the wind carry
your pain away."

00:39:22,881 --> 00:39:27,156
<i>"Let the waxing moon alight</i>
<i>the darkness within you."</i>

00:39:27,156 --> 00:39:31,131
And let this blood of
the powerful allow you to heal.

00:39:31,131 --> 00:39:33,102
My son, you shall be reborn.

00:39:33,102 --> 00:39:34,972
You shall be reborn.

00:39:34,972 --> 00:39:38,145
My son doesn't deserve to die.

00:39:38,145 --> 00:39:41,485
(sniffles)
I'm not an evil person.

00:39:41,485 --> 00:39:43,690
Ed told us
that they were healing spells.

00:39:43,690 --> 00:39:45,761
And-and medicine hadn't worked,

00:39:45,761 --> 00:39:48,500
and I was desperate
to try anything.

00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:50,637
Two people died because of this.

00:39:50,637 --> 00:39:52,775
The Book of Shadows
is very, very clear.

00:39:52,775 --> 00:39:56,048
It says that a spell
will only work

00:39:56,048 --> 00:39:58,186
if the sacrificed dies

00:39:58,186 --> 00:40:00,524
so that the other one can live.

00:40:02,261 --> 00:40:04,165
I had to save my boy.

00:40:05,634 --> 00:40:08,173
And you ended up
losing him anyway.

00:40:13,885 --> 00:40:15,655
Mason?

00:40:15,655 --> 00:40:16,757
I'm so sorry.

00:40:16,757 --> 00:40:17,826
Yeah.

00:40:17,826 --> 00:40:20,063
There anybody
I can call?

00:40:21,534 --> 00:40:22,769
Any family?

00:40:22,769 --> 00:40:24,640
Ever since my dad died,

00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:25,909
it's just been me and Mom.

00:40:25,909 --> 00:40:28,816
This is when I get dumped

00:40:28,816 --> 00:40:31,287
in an orphanage
with Oliver Twist, right?

00:40:31,287 --> 00:40:33,659
No, that's not
gonna happen.

00:40:33,659 --> 00:40:35,094
Sure.

00:40:35,094 --> 00:40:37,934
You still getting
your treatments?

00:40:37,934 --> 00:40:39,971
(sighs)
Yeah.

00:40:39,971 --> 00:40:41,842
I start a new round
of chemo next month.

00:40:41,842 --> 00:40:44,012
Doctors said they're gonna be
tweaking the protocols.

00:40:44,012 --> 00:40:46,585
(sighs)

00:40:46,585 --> 00:40:49,090
Think maybe things
might turn around.

00:40:52,663 --> 00:40:55,236
I'm homeless,

00:40:55,236 --> 00:40:57,006
but I'm not hopeless.

00:40:57,006 --> 00:41:00,981
HANNAH:
He can stay with my family.

00:41:02,116 --> 00:41:04,855
My parents already said
it was okay.

00:41:06,859 --> 00:41:08,263
Hannah, what...

00:41:08,263 --> 00:41:09,732
What are you doing here?

00:41:12,003 --> 00:41:13,973
I heard about your mom.

00:41:17,047 --> 00:41:18,716
I'm really sorry.

00:41:18,716 --> 00:41:20,788
Yeah, me, too.

00:41:22,157 --> 00:41:26,132
You've always been
really sweet to me,

00:41:26,132 --> 00:41:29,271
even when I was so mean to you.

00:41:34,249 --> 00:41:36,887
And I couldn't be more sorry.

00:41:38,157 --> 00:41:39,292
So...

00:41:39,292 --> 00:41:42,098
if you want to play kick the can
or something...

00:41:45,004 --> 00:41:47,008
We're not
little kids anymore, Hannah.

00:41:47,008 --> 00:41:49,312
I know that,

00:41:49,312 --> 00:41:51,016
but...

00:41:51,016 --> 00:41:53,688
what do you say?

00:42:00,268 --> 00:42:02,606
(laughs, sniffles)

00:42:04,076 --> 00:42:05,879
Come on, let's go.

00:42:09,654 --> 00:42:10,790
(sighs)

00:42:13,696 --> 00:42:14,931
Poor kid.

00:42:14,931 --> 00:42:18,773
How could a mother's love
get so twisted?

00:42:18,773 --> 00:42:21,912
Well, at least
Hannah stepped up.

00:42:22,681 --> 00:42:24,050
Kind of gives you hope, right?

00:42:27,624 --> 00:42:28,822
That'd be nice.

